[start section id="20102"]

Evaluation of a large colonic polyp.

[end section id="20102"]

[start section id="20103"]

Initially she was told it was upper rectal.  Underwent a colonoscopy today by Dr. Bradley Hendricks that clearly shows that it is in the sigmoid.  He tattooed the area below it.  Her past history is notable for having abdominal exploration for an ovarian cyst in her 20s but since then has had no other problems.  Family history is noted as a history of breast cancer but no colon cancer.

[end section id="20103"]


